Copper advanced for a second day,
paring the first weekly drop in four, as U.S. jobless claims
fell and manufacturing in  China  and the euro area grew more than
estimated, adding to signs of a global recovery.  Market News:  Metals News:  Metals Prices:  To contact the reporter on this story:
